Keep "Next" and "Finish" buttons in the same location on pages that follow each other.

So one of the painful aspects of using JIRA is that you have a lot of "next" "next" "next" "finish" clicking to do.  Now having multiple pages is ok.   What is not ok is that you have to move your mouse around after each click.   This makes it really tedious for doing the same task over and over.   (A good example of this is the:  "convert to sub-task")

Unifying the location of the "next" / "ok" / "finish" button on each page would be really nice.

